[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ex-footballer Adam Johnson loses appeal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ex-England footballer Adam Johnson has lost a Court of Appeal challenge against his conviction for sexual activity with a schoolgirl.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 29-year-old was jailed for six years last March for sexually touching and grooming the 15-year-old fan.
He was refused leave to appeal his conviction and sentence in July, but launched a second bid late last year.
A panel of three appeal judges turned down the former Sunderland player's latest bid.
